  <source>Peking University People's Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Allogeneic hematopoietic stem cell transplantation (HSCT) is currently the only curative
      treatment for myelodysplastic syndrome (MDS), especially for advanced MDS (blast &gt;5%).
      However, many patients cannot find an HLA-matched donor. haploidentical donor is an
      alternative stem cell source.

      the study hypothesis: Haploidentical/mismatched hematopoietic stem cell transplantation can
      improve the survival of patients with myelodysplastic syndrome
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
